{"itemid":1449,"subject":"LOCUS Nominees Announced","event":"<a href=\"http://ic.pics.livejournal.com/grrm/7059164/204172/204172_original.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"locus\" src=\"http://ic.pics.livejournal.com/grrm/7059164/204172/204172_300.jpg\" title=\"locus\" /></a>\r\n\r\n\r\nLOCUS, the premiere SF and fantasy newsletter/ fanzine/ semiprozine/ whatever -- an indispensible publication whatever you call it -- has just announced the finalists for this year&#39;s annual Locus Awards, and I am happy to announce that the list includes a couple nods for me.\r\n\r\n&quot;The Princess and the Queen,&quot; my &#39;fake history&#39; novella from DANGEROUS WOMEN, has been nominated as Best Novella.\r\n\r\nAnd OLD MARS, the retro-SF anthology I co-edited by Gardner Dozois, is a finalist for Best Anthology.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ic.pics.livejournal.com/grrm/7059164/204509/204509_original.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Old Mars cvr\" src=\"http://ic.pics.livejournal.com/grrm/7059164/204509/204509_300.jpg\" title=\"Old Mars cvr\" /></a>\r\n\r\nGargoo is competing against himself in the anthology category, since his annual BEST OF THE YEAR is also nominated.&nbsp; Gardner is also nominated as Best Editor (I&#39;m not).\r\n\r\nI&#39;m also thrilled by the nominations of a couple of stories we edited.&nbsp; Joe Abercrombie&#39;s &quot;Some Desperado&quot; from DANGEROUS WOMEN and Howard Waldrop&#39;s &quot;The Dead-Sea-Bottom Scrolls&quot; from OLD MARS are both finalists in Best Short Story.\r\n\r\nAnd while I had nothing to do with it, I&#39;m equally delighted by the nomination of ABADDON&#39;S GATE by my friends Daniel Abraham and Ty Franck as Best Novel.&nbsp; ABADDON&#39;S absence from this year&#39;s Hugo ballot is a crime, especially considering some of the stuff that <i>did</i> make that ballot.\r\n\r\nWin, lose, or draw, it is an honor just to be nominated.\r\n\r\nThe full list of nominees can found here:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.locusmag.com/News/2014/05/2014-locus-awards-finalists/\">http://www.locusmag.com/News/2014/05/2014-locus-awards-finalists/</a>","ditemid":370980,"eventtime":"2014-05-07 20:25:00","props":{"current_mood":"pleased","current_location":"Santa Fe","current_moodid":109,"commentalter":1399657634,"give_features":1,"picture_keyword":"thumbs up","opt_screening":"F","interface":"web","personifi_tags":"nterms:yes"},"can_comment":0,"logtime":"2014-05-08 02:25:48","anum":36,"url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/370980.html","event_timestamp":1399494300,"reply_count":10,"comments":[{"collapsed":0,"shown":1,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/67867104/2611870","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/370980.html?replyto=19094820","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/370980.html?thread=19094820#t19094820","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/370980.html?thread=19094820#t19094820","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/370980.html?thread=19094820#t19094820","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"brithistorian","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://brithistorian.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":19094820,"talkid":74589,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/370980.html?thread=19094820#t19094820","article":"Congratulations!","upictitle":"BritHistorian: sense of wonder SF","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","stime":"3 years ago","poster":"grrm","ctime":"May 8 2014, 02:28:31 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://brithistorian.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"brithistorian","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"brithistorian","user