cobian33","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://francobian33.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":19109156,"talkid":74645,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/370980.html?thread=19109156#t19109156","upictitle":"Franco Martin Bianchini: pic#121745144","article":"Great! Congratulations!<br />Just waiting for Dangeorus Women in Argentina.<br />","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 years ago","ctime":"May 8 2014, 20:21:32 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://francobian33.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"francobian33","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"francobian33","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://francobian33.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"francobian33","ctime_ts":1399580492,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/370980.html?replyto=19113508","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/370980.html?thread=19113508#t19113508","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/370980.html?thread=19113508#t19113508","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/370980.html?thread=19113508#t19113508","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"guessingo","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://guessingo.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":19113508,"talkid":74662,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/370980.html?thread=19113508#t19113508","upictitle":"guessingo: pic#0","article":"I have come to like anthologies. I actually like them more so I can find authors I have not read before. So if I see some stories in your anthologies by authors I like, Ill buy it and generally like the stories, however, the gems are when I find authors I never read before.<br /><br />The beauty of an anthology is that each story is a small time investment. I may like the author or a I may not, but I didn't spend alot of time on a story I may not like. Then if I like an authors short story Ill go look for that authors books. <br /><br />I believe George credited being in the same Legends anthology with Robert Jordan for helping to launch Song of Ice and Fire. I think I had already read George by then ( it was a long time, I can't remember), so I didn't discover George from that book. I did discuss Robert Silverburg and the Marjipoo stories. Im not that tuned into the SF/F community so I had never heard of him. <br /><br />Short Stories are also fun because they are different. Its a different style from a full length novel. As I get older, I really just want to read different types of stories. <br /><br />One last thing... the way Ty's careers is going we may be seeing just putting up 'help wanted' ads for a new assistant on his blog soon. Ty may not need the work anymore.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 years ago","ctime":"May 9 2014, 15:23:28 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"your anthologies introduces me to new authors","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://guessingo.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"guessingo","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"guessingo","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://guessingo.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"guessingo","ctime_ts":1399649008,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/91237832/7059164","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livej